<subSubSection id="48D355CA8FE1FE6F48A75796FE2BFCC6" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418FE1FE6F48A75796FEE2FF22" blockId="431.[151,760,151,210]" box="[151,327,186,210]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">
(
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FE1FE6F48905796FE9BFF22" box="[160,318,186,210]" captionStart="PLATE 136" captionStartId="430.[151,233,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[233,1357,273,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-52@430.[198,1388,253,1844]" captionTargetPageId="430" captionText="PLATE 136. Esagonatopus sinensis sp. nov., holotype. A. Chela. B. Mesosoma, lateral view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. Scale bar 0.10 mm for A, 0.40 mm for B and C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278850" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278850/files/figure.png" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Plate 136A–C</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418FE1FE6F48A7562EFC44FCE2" blockId="431.[151,1437,258,967]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FE1FE6F48A7562EFE0FFEEB" bold="true" box="[151,426,258,283]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Description of Female.</emphasis>
Apterous; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48FE1FE6F4AB2562EFD78FEEA" box="[642,733,258,282]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" unit="mm" value="3.9">3.9 mm</quantity>
. Head brown, except anterior third of face, clypeus, gena and mandible testaceous; antenna brown, except segments 1–2 testaceous and segment 10 whitish; mesosoma brown, except scutum and distal extremity of propodeum yellow-testaceous and testaceous nuances on propleuron, pronotum and metanotum; petiole black; metasoma brown; legs brown-testaceous. Antenna clavate; antennal segments in following proportions: 9:6:17:10:8:7:6:5:5:8. Head excavated, shiny, unsculptured; frontal line complete; occipital carina absent; temple absent; POL = 1.5; OL = 1; OOL = 7; greatest breadth of posterior ocelli about as long as POL. Palpal formula 6/2. Pronotum crossed by strong transverse impression, shiny, unsculptured. Scutum shiny, with few longitudinal striae, with two lateral pointed apophyses (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FE1FE6F4C0756D2FB7FFDE6" box="[1079,1242,510,534]" captionStart="PLATE 136" captionStartId="430.[151,233,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[233,1357,273,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-52@430.[198,1388,253,1844]" captionTargetPageId="430" captionText="PLATE 136. Esagonatopus sinensis sp. nov., holotype. A. Chela. B. Mesosoma, lateral view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. Scale bar 0.10 mm for A, 0.40 mm for B and C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278850" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278850/files/figure.png" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Plate 136B, C</figureCitation>
). Scutellum flat, shiny, unsculptured. Meso-metapleural suture almost completely obsolete, only shortly present on sides of metanotum. Metanotum shiny, unsculptured, flat, not hollow behind scutellum. Metathorax + propodeum shiny, unsculptured, with two small lateral pointed apophyses on sides of metanotum (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FE1FE6F4C3E5546FB0FFD72" box="[1038,1194,618,642]" captionStart="PLATE 136" captionStartId="430.[151,233,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[233,1357,273,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-52@430.[198,1388,253,1844]" captionTargetPageId="430" captionText="PLATE 136. Esagonatopus sinensis sp. nov., holotype. A. Chela. B. Mesosoma, lateral view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. Scale bar 0.10 mm for A, 0.40 mm for B and C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278850" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278850/files/figure.png" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Plate 136B, C</figureCitation>
). Mesopleuron partly unsculptured and partly transversely striate. Metapleuron and posterior surface of propodeum strongly transversely striate. Protarsal segments in following proportions: 13:3:6:17:25. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FE1FE6F4C68559EFB7CFD3A" box="[1112,1241,690,714]" captionStart="PLATE 136" captionStartId="430.[151,233,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[233,1357,273,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-52@430.[198,1388,253,1844]" captionTargetPageId="430" captionText="PLATE 136. Esagonatopus sinensis sp. nov., holotype. A. Chela. B. Mesosoma, lateral view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. Scale bar 0.10 mm for A, 0.40 mm for B and C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278850" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278850/files/figure.png" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Plate 136A</figureCitation>
) with one small subapical tooth and one row of seven peg-like hairs and one hair. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FE1FE6F4C9755FAFA83FD1E" box="[1191,1318,726,750]" captionStart="PLATE 136" captionStartId="430.[151,233,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[233,1357,273,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-52@430.[198,1388,253,1844]" captionTargetPageId="430" captionText="PLATE 136. Esagonatopus sinensis sp. nov., holotype. A. Chela. B. Mesosoma, lateral view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. Scale bar 0.10 mm for A, 0.40 mm for B and C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278850" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278850/files/figure.png" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Plate 136A</figureCitation>
) with one row of 19 lamellae; distal apex with at least 18 lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/0/1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418FE1FE6F48F75433FE2BFCC6" blockId="431.[151,1437,258,967]" box="[199,398,798,823]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FE1FE6F48F75433FEAEFCC7" bold="true" box="[199,267,799,823]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
